place_description: Specialty coffee shop focused on providing insight into the farmers, their lives, and the education of coffee WITHOUT JUDGEMENT. From savory breakfast sandwiches to our in-house bakes scones, enjoy a cup in the co-working space at 742 North and chillax to our smooth playlists.

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful experience and the coffee tastes so good.
Amazing staff experience & great coffee
Love me some Forte!! A local shop nestled in "742 North" building that sources and roasts their own beans.  Barista team is fantastic, and Perrin's scones and breakfast treats are unique and awesome!
My fav!
Tara rocks the free world.

Breakfast Sammy and chai tea were phenomenal! So many yummy pastry treats it was hard to decide what to get. The batista was very sweet and knowledgeable and I will definitely be returning. The coffee shop was in a cool looking co-working space, can't wait to come and get some work done and drink some delicious coffee!

Love coming to this hidden gem of Rock Hill! The baristas are so helpful and delightful! The house made goods are always on point. Love how they switch weekly flavors.
my favorite is the cold brew with oat milk with some sweetness. I let the baristas pick the flavors and it is always a win!
The best coffee in the world. Period.

Friendly  very knowledgeable
Best beans. Best bakery items.

I cannot put into words just how great and awesome this first time visit for me was here to this coffee house.
The vibe the set up is so unique you gotta get here and try this out!!
Let me start with the coffee. It was on point. It gets five stars the service it was on point and if there was a way to give 10 stars, I would give them 10 stars.
Warm, sincere, smiling, and you can definitely walk in and just feel the incredible positive energy .
My barista and I hope I'm spelling your name Craig her name was Alyssa and she really made the experience for me. Just something special.
Special shout out to her.
Cook Vibe
Enjoy the coffee and atmosphere! Make sure to grab an in-house scone!
Best coffee ever
THE BEST coffee place hands down!!!!

Best coffee in town. Coffee beans are graded on scale with 100 being the best, and places like Starbucks uses beans below 65, while Forte only uses beans 80 or higher (it could be higher than that, but definitely at least that high; and you can definitely tell. Staff is super friendly and I'm still testing to see if Elise or Tara make the best "Frog in a Blender", the top secret, off menu, specialty drink with green tea matcha as the primary input....

Great coffee and drinks!!
The ladies are amazing
My favorite coffee place! Great vibes, chill place and friendly service! We love Forte

Forte is just a great coffee shop through and through! I've been a regular since I tried them in November last year, from the service to the fresh pastries and quick service, I am constantly reminded why I keep coming back!!! - Ps ALWAYS pick the "Trust Fall" option you won't be disappointed!
Great coffee,food ,and vibes !

We were passing through on our way home from Carrowinds and stopped in for a cup of coffee. I was not expecting to have the best latte of my entire life! I'm not even exaggerating even a little bit! I believe the lady behind the counter was the owner, she was super friendly and definitely knew a lot about coffee! I had the frappe with caramelized peanut sauce and white chocolate.  I am not kidding when I say I have made it my life's mission to recreate this latte at home! Please tell me where I can get the peanut sauce from, it's so good!!!!!!
Great coffee and atmosphere. It is hidden in a weird looking building but worth finding if you like coffee. Definitely one of the best places in Rock Hill.
Really liked this coffee shop. Barista was knowledgeable, professional and kind. Atmosphere is really good. Inside and some outside seating as well

This coffee shop is a favorite of mine!!! Elise is such a sweetheart, she makes everyone feel so welcome there. They make great tasting coffee and food. This is great place for business meetings as well.

We are hardcore coffee enthusiasts. We never do flights because they're typically super sweet and heavy on the dairy. (Babe is lactose-intolerant.) We were so excited that one of their flight options included cold brew, your choice of drip coffee, espresso, and one seasonal latte option. We chose the bee's knees latte (vanilla, cinnamon, and honey). Highly recommend the experience if you're serious about coffee.
Can I add stars for atmosphere? Seriously, the best coffee spot ever. Go here. Go, go, go, and go again!

The coffee was delicious and the barista was awesome. We went there to try the " Coffee Blendie" which is an espresso blended drink. It was so good. I loved the consistency and the undertone of flavors that heightened the espresso. We also had a seasonal drink that was great. The barista was so nice and accommodating. She told us if we didn't like her suggestion she would happily make us another drink. If you're in the Rockhill, SC area then stop and grab a cup of coffee.

Love the coffee and the baristas . Definitely try the "forte favs" on the menu  my favorites are the island time and the lavender haze or get a "trust fall". Also try a scone they are second to none! The building is super cool too with lots of local businesses of all different types. Definitely check this place out!

This is a great, safe space to get work done. You can have your own private space or be in the open. I get a lot of work done here & it helps me remain focused. I'm not big on coffee, but I always buy a frappe to show my support of the establishment. It's a great location. There's nothing to complain about here, so don't complain.
Fun vibes in the place, always the nicest people working the counter. Love to see what they've done with the place.

Love this little shop. Has a nice eclectic relaxing home feel to it. The staff was friendly and very helpful. I got the bees knees and it instantly became my go to drink. You definitely need to check this place out. They have books and I think I saw board games against the wall as well. I could absolutely spend a few hours here meeting a few friends or holding casual Interviews.
Excellent coffee, service and vibe. A must stop destination.
One of my favorite places to get coffee in Rock Hill. If you know what good expresso tastes like and need some this is the place to go!
Great atmosphere and coffee

Forte Legato never disappoints! Love when I walk in and Elise knows my drink order every time. If you're looking for strong, great tasting coffee and excellent customer service, then Forte is your place! Support your local small business and I promise you won't be disappointed! Try the iced brown sugar vanilla latte. :)
Great vibe to work or just hang out and drink some coffee.
Wasn't sure whar to expect when pulling up to the building.  Set up with plenty of workspace and micro offices.  Drinks were really tasty.

Really grateful for them. One of my favorite locally owned small businesses, eclectic and good quality loose leaf tea and pastries.  Love the hang out, welcoming space. Hope to see you guys partner with cooks and bakers to have more lunch options. Please offer those of us coming with coffee lovers, coffee substitute options such as chicory root, dandelion, roasted barley and mushroom "coffee"  Love your teas!!! Would love to see you offer these as well!
This is the only place I have found that makes a great Mocha- not too much chocolate  not too bland. People are super nice too.
The espresso class was a great date night!
Great coffee, great people, and the spinach feta bomb will have you coming back for more.
Really unique co-working space. The coffee was really good and the barista was very friendly and knowledgeable. They have some pretty rare coffees too and the community connection is really nice.

Fresh brewed coffee, specialty coffee drinks, delicious scones, muffins, breakfast sandwiches. Cool calm atmosphere.  Staff is always friendly, personable, extremely engaging and helpful. Great at suggesting new drinks to try. Fabulous fruit drinks! Cozy seating.
Great little coffee shop in the 742 business center.
Cinderella bread is so good!!!!
This is a great small coffee shop that gives a great vibe and relaxing. It's also great that it's next to a college so the students can do their work and drink coffee or eat. Very nice place
Cameroon coffee is excellent!  Espresso is also good. Service is outstanding!
Nice coffee place with a fun and welcoming atmosphere. Glad to see they had sugar free options. Great customer service.
Great coffee
I stop in a couple times a week, staff is always friendly. Coffee is always good. Plenty of tables if you want to hang out, read a book, study, etc.
Best coffee shop ever. 10/10 recommend
I absolutely love this place. The manager is really nice. I always look forward to getting a coffee there once in a while. Keep being amazing.
Coffee flights! Holiday coffee specials, great prices, friendly service, huge work space, comfy couches, breakfast pastries .... all around just an amazing hidden gem.
Nice coffee. Finally an alternative toStarbucks

Went early in the morning, about 15 minutes after they opened for a sandwich and coffee. Barista was friendly, and helped me customize a fall drink which turned out great. Sandwich was done quickly and it was tasty, although the cheese was on the outside of one piece. I just flipped it and it worked. Price was reasonable and i enjoyed it, great spot all in all
Can't say enough about the service and quality of coffee and food. Shared a coffee flight, Croissant breakfast sandwich, and pumpkin muffin. All wonderful. Highly recommend this gem!
Coffee flight and breakfast sandwich was delicious! The service is always phenomenal and it's a great place to work!

Both the service and coffee were excellent. We tried the pumpkin coffee flight: my favorites were pumpkin pie and toasty pumpkin. I mixed the two together and it was the perfect cup of iced coffee. My daughter had the bacon, egg, and cheese on ciabatta and said it was really good. The people are so nice and welcoming. We stayed and got a little work done while grooving to the reggae music lightly playing in the background.

By far the best coffee in Rock Hill or for 50 miles in any direction! If you haven't already stopped in to check this place out, I can't recommend them enough. They do all their own roasting! Buy it by the cup or by the by the bag. Take it home and make your own cup. However you want it, Forte Legato has got a beverage for you!

This was my first time visiting. They're located inside a co-working space at 742 North but it's super easy to park and just walk right in. They have coffee (hot and cold), pastries, non coffee drinks etc. I recommend the coffee blende.....top note!

This is a nice little coffee shop. It's a nice break from Starbucks. The coffee even tastes better. It's either the coffee bean they use or the love they put into every cup. I bet that nice fancy coffee machine they have that came all the way from Italy has something to do with it too.
Bring back the cruffin.

Not what I was expecting! This is a coffee stand in a shared building where it seems like a shared meeting space. Yummy iced chai and blueberry loaf, and it was so pleasant to work here for a little while!

This coffee shop was referred to me. I was getting tired of Dunkin and Starbucks so I thought I would give it a try. I ordered a Caramel Blendie which at the time of ordering assumed was a frappe. The blendie was great, but compared to Starbucks Caramel Frappe it didn't quite hold up for me. The coffee was too strong for my taste. They did offer more items on the menu that I want to try so I'll definitely be back.

I rarely get out of bed for anything.... willingly, but Perrin's scones. ugh.. They are my guilty pleasure. Just the right consistency because we know all know consistency is key when baking scones. Paired with Elise's turtle on the rocks. Yes, God yes! My mouth screams with pleasure. All is right with the world once I consume these tasty little mouth O's. Can I get an Oh YEEEEAAHHHH.

And now, I must work. Thanks Girls! Love you!
This coffee is not to my taste, however service was excellent!! You should try them for yourself and decide.

Really excellent service!! The woman with bright red hair (I didn't get her name), was so sweet and took her time to give me recommendations and answer questions. Their coffee is excellent! So happy there's an actual shop for them now. I'd previously been getting their coffee through a different restaurant in town. Great over all atmosphere. Can't wait to have coffee dates here!

Went in to get 2 large coffees and 3 people were in front of me. After 10 minutes I was told that someone would be with me (because the only person working in the kitchen area had a door dash or one of those shady food delivery people behind the counter and he did not wash his hands when he went behind the counter either) after 6 more minutes  I left and will not be back. To be honest they were my least favorite overly priced coffee shop anyway but where way less busy so I made the mistake of going back. Now I know why they weren't as busy as the rest. You want  a good cup of coffee..... go to Mado.
great breakfast sandwiches and coffee refills

This is by far my fav coffee shop in the area. The coffee is delicious, the staff is, really, beyond wonderful (I cannot say enough great things about them). I enjoy ever visit here and love introducing people to them! Thanks for existing and being wonderful!

I have to update my response. I still feel passionately about this being my favorite coffee shop!!! Their pastry case is continuing to impress me more and more. Perrin has been doing a lot of the baking and I HAVE YET!! To try something short of delicious. Very excited they are able to do things in house and have been enjoying this development very very much. Coffee still the absolute best!!!
Fresh roasted coffee, never more than a few days old, accompanied by delicious, locally baked pastries and more all day! Worth a special trip.
Great iced coffee drinks and smoothies. Very tasty. If you're vegan, they have plenty of drink options. No vegan pastries though  Service was friendly and fast. Nice decor.
Best cup of coffee in the Rock Hill/Ft. Mill area. Flavors don't overpower the coffee and the beans they use have a great taste.

Best coffee in Rock Hill. I highly recommend this hidden gem, tucked away in a small business complex. The service was excellent with such a friendly barista. She had the type of energy that makes your day better just from a quick chat. Plenty of seating, outlets for your electronics and good Wi-Fi. The biggest reason for my five stars is the coffee. I had one of the best hot lattes that I've had in years. It wasn't the cheapest coffee in town but certainly worth every penny. I'll definitely be making a trip back next time I'm anywhere near the area.
Friendly people, but the nitro I got was watery.
This place is the best
Good coffee
We went there thinking it would be a coffee shop. Regardless , their coffees are good!
Yummy coffee and good selection of bakery items from local bakers.
Have been coming here for months and am always happy to get a good drink and a good conversation with the baristas!
The best coffee ever I suggest you try it and when you do you will not look at other coffee the same

I really like this place. I always use the app and order ahead so I've never had an issue with waiting as a few others have mentioned. I also get curbside to go. My drinks are usually ready by the time I get there (10ish minutes). The two ladies that work there are always super friendly and offer suggestions. I like that they offer non-dairy milk and also let you customize the drinks. I've only had issues with the app twice and it was just that it would freeze up. Otherwise everything is always great!

I absolutely love this coffee shop in Rock Hill 
This is the best ice coffee, marble macchiato.
Great coffee! Great breakfast bagel! Great service!

Don't go here if you need to run. To be honest poor customer service.  I waited 20 min for a single cup of coffee maybe 25. I was second in line.  Not sure it was worth the wait.  Not even a sorry for the long wait.  Won't be coming back.
No complaints from me. Just some good coffee.
Kiosk style counter inside, with other small businesses. Friendly people, diverse menu options and bagged coffee for sale.
Thank you for hosting Ladies Game night!  Loved your peach smoothie!

Wonderful coffee! I had the French Provence (vanilla lavender) and my hubby got the pour over (Costa Rica). The lounge area is fun and comfortable. The people working there were so friendly and welcoming. They even invited us to their church. A taste of community here. We are definitely going back for more coffee! Yum!

Quirky set-up and a very friendly team.
Lots of seating indoor and outdoor, but the coffee was a let down for me, especially after being a regular at BoCo Coffee Company.

Nothing forte about Forte Legato Coffee, nor was the coffee a latte as ordered.

The pastries looked great and their coffee/espresso machine is quite unique. Will give it another try if BoCo is closed, but recommend Mado Bakery for coffee and pastries.

This is a kiosk type coffee counter inside a building that holds multiple business.  They have pastries and all the coffee types you could want.  I got an Americano and it was good. Their coffee is very acidic, which is great if you like acidic coffee.  The pastry was delicious.
They are not open on Sunday. They do host food trucks in the parking lot on Thursday evenings.
Forte Legato Coffee is awesome!  The coffees are yummy,  the staff is friendly and knowledgeable.  When in town, I try to get by to enjoy a latte and take home some beans!  Love this place.
Great Drip coffee, the Ethiopian is my favorite. Good espresso drinks as well and super friendly staff! This is legit coffee!
Wonderful Coffee!!  Great place to meet-up with a friend.

Lovely visit here!
Fabulous coffee-- specifically catered to what I was in the mood for.
Really awesome owner & helpers! Loved every minute of my visit.

Fantastic variety of whole bean coffee including unusual small crop/farm options from around the world. Delightfully roasted with excellent espresso and tea flavors and options they also have tasty local baked goods for sale.
Theres lots of coffee options in Rock Hill and Charlotte metro area but really only one you need as your go to, and this is it.

LOVE this place and the coffee! It's a warm, open atmosphere and the staff are always friendly. The stories of where the coffee comes from and those relationships with the growers. The 742 N building is up and coming and I'm excited to see it!

Nick and his crew at Forte Legato are the absolute best! They had wonderful coffee, food, and the service is wonderful. They have indoor and outdoor seating for you to sit and hang out at. If you need coffee, support a locally owned business!

Their Carmel Blendie is absolutely amazing, by far my favorite coffee drink in Rock Hill!  I love that you can order online and they will even deliver out to your car.  Great place to have a networking meeting or work quietly if you need to get out of the house.

Forte Legato is one of my favorite coffee shops. All their coffee drinks are delicious and they have a good variety of beans you can buy too. The customer service is also top-notch! Support local coffee shops and check them out!

This place is AWESOME.  And I dig the name.  They serve a lovely nitro coldbrew, though my fantastic barista feared it was a mite weak.  As a 2pm pick-me-up, it was perfect.  Great internet, spacious seating, excellent interwebz.  I'm a fan.  Oh.  And I got my photo made with RBG. #notorious

Customer service was great. Atmosphere is warm, relaxed and cozy. As a die hard tea person, I would like to see a few more tea options. That being said, the quality of the available tea is very good. They use good quality loose leaf teas and brew them in convenient,  disposable satchels.

Overall, a nice place.

Very nice, roomy, and well lit seating area. Great location on Anderson Road. Service very friendly. Got the Intermezzo blend coffee. Delicious way to start the day. Look forward to trying some if their lattes
Very clean, cute and great customer service.  Coffee was delicious with a great menu to choose from

Besides the coffee, something has to be said for great customer service. This was by far the warmest and friendliest coffee shop I have had the pleasure of being to. My cappuccino was made perfectly, I learned about the most desirable milk for baristas and even some about the building. I'm a coffee NUT and will be back, highly recommended.
Great coffee, nice people.
Best coffee in the Carolinas in my opinion.  Family-owned business by great people!
Best coffee. Best service. Great new space. Very excited to have this here.
Great customer service, their new location had a lovely and friendly atmosphere, along with the workers themselves. I would definitely recommend coming here.
